---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="The Curriculum"
  description="One curriculum from infancy to AI mastery, in three pillars: an evidence-based pedagogy, AI that empowers teachers, and AI mastery for children."
>
  <section class="wrap intro">
    <p class="eyebrow rise rise-1">The curriculum</p>
    <h1 class="rise rise-2">One curriculum, from infancy to AI mastery.</h1>
    <p class="lede rise rise-3">
      This is not a new pedagogy invented from scratch. It is a free, open
      synthesis of what already works, extended with the one dimension the
      existing efforts predate: the arrival of capable AI, pointed deliberately
      at empowerment rather than surveillance.
    </p>
    <p class="lede-2 rise rise-3">
      Pillar 1, the curriculum, is the heart of the framework and runs from
      infancy. Pillar 2 supports the adults who deliver it. Pillar 3, AI
      mastery, is the capstone, built on top once a child has the knowledge to
      judge a machine.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap pillar" id="pillar-1">
    <div class="pillar-head">
      <span class="pillar-num">Pillar 1</span>
      <h2>An open, evidence-based pedagogy</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar-body">
      <p>
        A complete, age-banded curriculum and methods guide that any teacher or
        parent can adopt without permission or payment. It rests on one
        principle, expressed in three developmental forms: an adult guides the
        child's mental effort toward a clear goal, at a difficulty that is hard
        but achievable, starting from the child's actual level.
      </p>
      <ul class="bands">
        <li><strong>Foundations, birth to six.</strong> Guided play, rich language, movement, and self-regulation.</li>
        <li><strong>Building, six to ten.</strong> The explicit-instruction years: systematic decoding, concrete-to-pictorial-to-abstract mathematics, daily retrieval and spaced practice, and teaching each child at their actual level.</li>
        <li><strong>Deepening, ten to twelve.</strong> Knowledge applied through projects, structured inquiry, teaching younger peers, and the AI-mastery work of Pillar 3.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="beneath">
        Beneath all three: sleep, movement, play, and a present adult who talks
        and listens.
      </p>
      <div class="practical">
        <p class="practical-label">Start doing it today</p>
        <p>
          <strong><a href="/resources/foundations-first-three-years">Foundations: The First Three Years</a></strong>
          is the first concrete, stage-by-stage module: what is developing at
          each stage from birth to three, the specific activities to do this
          week, and how to tell it is working. No apps, no cost.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a class="text-link" href="/resources/pillar-1-curriculum">Read the full MYCELIUM Learning Framework <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap pillar" id="pillar-2">
    <div class="pillar-head">
      <span class="pillar-num">Pillar 2</span>
      <h2>AI that empowers teachers</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar-body">
      <p>
        An AI in the room can give a teacher understanding they would never get
        otherwise. The correction is the target: it listens to the teaching, not
        to the children's feelings. It gives every teacher a private coach,
        reflecting back the patterns of a lesson as formative feedback, and
        turns coaching from a scarce luxury into something every teacher can
        have.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        <p>
          By constitution, this tool must never infer a child's emotion or inner
          state, never score or profile children, and never replace the
          teacher's relationship with the child. It is owned by the teacher and
          private to the teacher. Its data belongs to the person being
          developed, not to the institution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap pillar" id="pillar-3">
    <div class="pillar-head">
      <span class="pillar-num">Pillar 3</span>
      <h2>AI mastery for children</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar-body">
      <p>
        Children will live and work inside AI for life. The goal is to make them
        its masters and editors, not its passive consumers. Built for the
        deepening years, it teaches children to use AI as a thinking partner
        they control, to audit its output for hallucination and bias, to
        understand how it works and fails, and to reason about its ethics.
      </p>
      <p>
        The governing test never changes: if the AI increases how much the child
        thinks, it is a tutor; if it replaces the child's thinking, it is a
        crutch that quietly weakens them. For what these systems are and why
        mastery beats banning, start with <a href="/resources/understanding-ai">Understanding AI</a>.
      </p>
      <div class="pillar-links">
        <a class="text-link" href="/resources/understanding-ai">Understanding AI <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="text-link" href="/resources/pillar-3-teacher-workbook">Teacher Workbook, ages 10 to 12 <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="text-link" href="/resources/pillar-3-part-ii-frontier">The Frontier, ages 12 to 14 <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="text-link" href="/resources/school-implementation-guide">School implementation guide <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .intro { padding-top: 3.5rem; max-width: 48rem; }
  .intro h1 { font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5.5vw, 3.6rem); margin: 0.6rem 0 0; }
  .lede { font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--color-ink-soft); margin-top: 1.2rem; }
  .lede-2 { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--color-ink-soft); margin-top: 1rem; }

  .pillar {
    margin-top: 3.5rem;
    padding-top: 3rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    scroll-margin-top: 6rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .pillar { grid-template-columns: 16rem minmax(0, 1fr); gap: 3rem; }
  }
  .pillar-num {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-clay);
  }
  .pillar-head h2 { font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3.4vw, 2.3rem); margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
  .pillar-body { max-width: 46rem; }
  .pillar-body > * + * { margin-top: 1.1rem; }
  .pillar-body p { color: var(--color-ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .bands { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1.2rem 0 0; display: grid; gap: 0.8rem; }
  .bands li {
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }
  .bands li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0; top: 0.6em;
    width: 0.42rem; height: 0.42rem;
    background: var(--color-clay);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
  .bands strong { color: var(--color-ink); }
  .beneath { font-style: italic; }
  .practical {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    background: var(--color-pine-tint);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-pine) 20%, var(--color-line));
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-pine);
    border-radius: 0.6rem;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem;
  }
  .practical p { margin: 0; }
  .practical-label {
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-clay);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem !important;
  }
  .callout p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-ink-soft); }
  .text-link { display: inline-block; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; }
  .pillar-links { display: grid; gap: 0.6rem; margin-top: 1.4rem; }
</style>
